message.content:
To calculate the Quick Ratio, we need to include only those current assets that can be quickly converted to cash. These “quick assets” are:

• Cash on Hand  
• Bank Deposits  
• Interest Receivable  
• Accounts Receivable  

Inventory is not included.

Step 1. Sum the quick assets at the end of the reporting period:

• Cash on Hand = 735892.55  
• Bank Deposits = 103027.27  
• Interest Receivable = 2566.71  
• Accounts Receivable = 2923459.19  

Total Quick Assets = 735892.55 + 103027.27 + 2566.71 + 2923459.19 = 3764945.72

Step 2. Identify Total Current Liabilities (end amount):

• Total Current Liabilities = 2736025.72

Step 3. Calculate the Quick Ratio:

Quick Ratio = Total Quick Assets / Total Current Liabilities  
Quick Ratio = 3764945.72 / 2736025.72 ≈ 1.38

Thus, the Quick Ratio is approximately 1.38.

The answer in the required JSON format is:

{"solution": {"Quick Ratio": "1.38"}}
